social_posts.post_text: Sears, Roebuck, & Co from FW 1939-40 • Vogue April 1948
🥴 stay away from door handles + hold open your own doors 😭 thanks so much for the beautiful repair @scienceandkindness ❤️‍🩹

Purchased this midriff dress from @collecting_dust_vtg a while back! The top never fit me too well but I was lucky enough to find another skirt in the same material. I was so grateful @newagainvintage49 was able to use that skirt to skillfully remake the top for me in a better size! Really recommend her work and appreciate @margaretthethird and @monicajveronicadesigns for suggesting her! 

Also sharing this image of a lady in the same belt border print in the 1940s — from a kind person in one of my many vintage Facebook groups.

What if I told you these dansk candle stick holders cost more than the broyhill dining set? …And that the candlestick holders were $52 …and that I reupholstered those chairs with a $2 upholstery scrap I had in my stash for years.
$20 Bonnie Cashin at the thrift? I’ll bite
This year’s Christmas card featuring some digital colorization and appropriating some 1948 graphic elements from designer, Tapio Wirkkala.
